{
  "text": "PARP-1 has been shown to play a role in chromatin structure [CITATION_1] . Chromatin conformation has been shown to differ between alleles for rs7903146 in human pancreatic islets [CITATION_2] . Interestingly, there have been other reports suggesting that the TCF7L2 and PARP-1 proteins interact [CITATION_3] , and indeed was confirmed in our previous study through the utilization of co-immunoprecipitation [CITATION_4] . Also, PARP-1 knockout mice have been shown to be protected from induced diabetes [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] . Since PARP-1 inhibitors have already been used in humans for oncologic indications, compounds like Olaparib could be used potentially to reduce PARP-1 inhibitory effects on TCF7L2. We hypothesized that Olaparib-mediated PARP-1 inhibition would therefore result in activation of TCF7L2, and yield a net GLP-1 agonist effect.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "8469953",
    "[CITATION_2]": "9634554",
